        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/f/b77776/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2019-07-14T17:28:02.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-post=\"4\" data-topic=\"153388\">\n<blockquote>\n<p>Fred,</p>\n<p>I think one of the keys to what makes Ramonet great is the balance and elegance.</p>\n<p>I also think 2013 has turned out really well for whites. I\u2019m currently sucking down a '13 PYCM St Aubin \u2018Le Banc\u2019 watching the world cup cricket and its in fine form.</p>\n<p>Cheers<br>\nJeremy</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Agree on both counts Jeremy!</p>\n<p>I suspect the initially poorly received 2013 vintage may end up being very good to excellent for both red and white alike.</p>",
